We have a Confluence connect macro (outputType "block") that works great as long as we do not nest it inside other Confluence macros. If we nest the macro, when requesting the macro details by /rest/api/content/ID/history/ID/macro/id/ID we just get a 404 response.

Without nesting everything is okay:

{noformat}
curl -u myuser https://myhost.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/29169283/history/26/macro/id/5816c11d-068e-5adc-b511-40b2a7736eff 
response: 
{"name":"latex-macro-block","body":"\\frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!} = \\binom{n}{k}","_links":{"base":"https://myhost.atlassian.net/wiki","context":"/wiki"}}
{noformat}

But if we add our macro to the contents of another macro, we get a 404 response:

{noformat}
curl -u myuser https://myhost.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/29169283/history/25/macro/id/5816c11d-068e-5adc-b511-40b2a7736eff
response:
{"statusCode":404,"data":{"authorized":false,"valid":true,"errors":[]},"message":"No macro found on content id : ContentId{id=29169283} with version: 25 and macroId: 5816c11d-068e-5adc-b511-40b2a7736eff"}
{noformat}

Is this a known problem? Any workarounds possible?

Please find attached the Confluence storage format with a nested macro that causes this issue.

Thanks in advance,
Michael

In one of our recent projects we noticed that the pagination of CQL results didn't work as expected. We were doing the following CQL search:

{code:none}
type = page AND (ancestor = 123 OR id = 123)
{code}

The limit was set to 200 results per page.
We noticed that the second page of the search results often also contained entries of the first page. The behaviour seemed to be random. Sometimes it overlapped with about 50 results and other times there were no overlappings at all.

We could workaround the problem by adding a "ORDER BY" to the CQL:

{code:none}
type = page AND (ancestor = 123 OR id = 123) ORDER BY title
{code}

I declared a {{web-resource}} for the {{atl.general}} context in my atlassian-plugin.xml. When creating a page, given JavaScript file is loaded and executed, but when I try to edit the page and enter the Confluence editor, in many cases it is not. Exiting and entering the editor a few times in a row sometimes leads to the JavaScript resource being loaded & executed again.

Excerpt from atlassian-plugin.xml
{code:xml}
<web-resource key="my-plugin-resources" name="my-plugin Web Resources">
    <dependency>com.atlassian.auiplugin:ajs</dependency>

    <data key="resource-path-data" class="com.example.MyDataProvider"/>
    <resource type="download" name="script.js" location="META-INF/resources/webjars/example/script.js"/>

    <context>atl.general</context>
</web-resource>
{code}

It's the same with the Confluence-specific {{editor}} and {{main}} contexts.

I don't think there is a way to reproduce this reliably; I think it just occurs from time to time when entering the editor.

Any ideas?

*Edit: SOLUTION*

The issue was caused by the "quick edit" functionality.
{code:javascript}
AJS.toInit(function () {
    // executed for a full page load
});

AJS.bind('init.rte', function() {
    // executed for partial page reloads, e.g. "quick edit"
});
{code}

